data.text: The owners daughter aggressively attacked a group of my friends completely unprovoked and no help or assistance was given from the owner. Would not feel safe going there.
data.name: Finn Malthouse
data.responseFromOwnerText:
Hi Finn

That's not how it went down as well you know, maybe you'll remember better in the morning?

If not, let me tell you...

Some of your 'unprovoked' friends were fighting in the marquee, near the TV, when we intervened.
Now I know its embarrassing when an 18 year old girl throws you big and tough lads out, but there's no need to get straight behind your keyboard.

It's probably best we did not help nor assist or it could have been more than your pride bruised, and anyway she looked like she had your measure. And can I say... wow!, just wow!, the names you called that girl! Your mum would be so proud! Is this how you treat all women or just the ones you look down on, like bar staff and waitresses?

Anyway thanks for the name, it'll go well with the incident report and CCTV that's on its way to the Police and everyone in pubwatch. We look forward to finding out everyone involved names so we can strongly suggest not one of you are allowed in any pub or restaurant in Wilmslow, Alderley Edge or the surrounding areas for the rest of the year.  We may even publish them as a warning to all that we do not
tolerate intimidation, violence or abuse aimed our staff in any licenced premises in Wilmslow.

Happy lockdown.
